                        </button>
                        </h2>
                        <div id="collapseOne" class="accordion-collapse collapse show" aria-labelledby="headingOne" data-bs-parent="#accordionExample">
                            <div class="accordion-body">
                                <strong>Tesla Model 3</strong> <br> 
                                <img id="TeslaModel3" src = "https://carwow-uk-wp-3.imgix.net/tesla-model-3-4.jpg" alt="Tesla Model 3" 
                                width="400"
                                height="250" >
                                <li> Class-leading range, performance and handling</li>
                                <li> Comfortable seating and lots of interior room</li>
                                <li> Access to Tesla's prolific Supercharger fast-charging stations </li>
                                <li> Starting price : £42,990 </li>
                                The Model 3 delivers an impressive driving experience compared to other non-luxury electric vehicles. Its minimalistic interior design feels chic, modern and upscale. The rear-wheel-drive layout and powerful electric motor also provide natural athleticism and quicker acceleration than anything in its price range. If you're in the market for an electric vehicle, the Model 3 is virtually unbeatable for the price.
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="accordion-item">
                        <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingTwo">
                        <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseTwo" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseTwo">
                            Best Luxury Electric Car Of The Year
                        </button>
                        </h2>
                        <div id="collapseTwo" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="headingTwo" data-bs-parent="#accordionExample">
                            <div class="accordion-body">
                                <strong> Porsche Taycan </strong>
                                <img id="PorscheTaycan" src="https://newsroom.porsche.com/.imaging/mte/porsche-templating-theme/image_1290x726/dam/pnr/2021/Products/Free-Software-Update-Taycan/Free-Software-Update-for-early-Porsche-Taycan_2.jpeg/jcr:content/Free%20Software-Update%20for%20early%20Porsche%20Taycan_2.jpeg" alt="PorscheTaycan"
                                width="400"
                                height="250" >
                
                                <li> Rapid acceleration and enjoyable, hunkered-down handling </li>
                                <li> Potential for very quick fast-charging capability </li>
                                <li> Four-door practicality plus two trunks </li>
                                <li> Impressive build quality and interior finish </li>
                                <li> Starting price:  £70,690 </li>
                                The Taycan represents Porsche's foray into the electric vehicle space, and it does not disappoint. The Taycan is a technological masterpiece that manages to deliver incredible comfort and effortless driving one moment and then, with the twist of a knob, world-beating performance the next. How one car can do both so well is a little baffling.
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="accordion-item">
                        <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingThree">
                        <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseThree" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseThree">
                            Best Electric SUV Of The Year
                        </button>
                        </h2>
                        <div id="collapseThree" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="headingThree" data-bs-parent="#accordionExample">
                            <div class="accordion-body">
                                <strong> Ford Mustang Mach-E </strong>
                                <img id = "FordMustang" alt="Ford Mustang Mach-E" img src="https://media.ford.com/content/fordmedia/fna/us/en/products/evs/mustang-mach-e/mustang-mach-e/jcr:content/content/media-section-parsys/textimage_f597/image.img.951.535.jpg/1608221793793.jpg"
                                width="400"
                                height="250" >
                                <li> Sporty handling and acceleration especially with the GT </li>
                                <li> Plenty of range with the larger battery pack </li>
                                <li> Big center touchscreen looks great and is pretty easy to use </li>
                                <li> Useful amount of cargo space </li>
                                <li> Starting price: £42,530 </li>
                                It's a Mustang! It's an SUV! It's the all-electric Ford Mach-E! We didn't know what to expect when we heard Ford was cooking up an electric Mustang SUV, but we're certainly glad it exists. With engaging driving performance, no tailpipe emissions and over-the-air software updates on a huge center touchscreen, the Mach-E drives and looks like a car of the future.
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </article>
